## 2. Final Copy & Section Order (Homepage)

### Section 1: The Linear-Style Hero
*Purpose: 3-second comprehension + immediate UI proof.*
*   **Eyebrow:** Platform Update: V2 Now Available.
*   **H1:** Stop Missing Calls. Start Scaling Revenue.
*   **Subheadline:** The automated operations platform for local service businesses. NexaOS instantly replies to missed calls, routes dispatching, and captures five-star reviews while your team is on the job.
*   **Primary CTA:** Deploy NexaOS Today
*   **Secondary CTA:** Watch the Product Demo
*   **Centerpiece Asset:** Floating, interactive Hero Loop (See Section 6).

### Section 2: The Honest Proof Stack (Marquee)
*Purpose: Leverage partner credibility without faking numbers.*
*   **Header:** Built to integrate with the systems you rely on.
*   **Logos (Greyscale, 30% opacity):** QuickBooks, Google Business Profile, Twilio, Stripe, Yelp.

### Section 3: The Threat (Problem Identification)
*Purpose: Agitate the pain logically.*
*   **H2:** If you are not first to reply, you have already lost the bid.
*   **Body:** Homeowners do not leave voicemail. They call the next company on their list. Every unanswered call is a $500 to $5,000 job handed directly to your competitor. We fix that immediately.

### Section 4: The Bento Box Grid (Features & UI)
*Purpose: Structural presentation of the 3 core pillars.*

*   **Block A (2/3 width, Top): Missed Call Recovery**
    *   *Headline:* Infinite Inbound Capacity.
    *   *Body:* Never send a lead to voicemail again. Automated SMS replies engage the customer instantly, securely capturing the lead details directly into your pipeline.
    *   *Visual:* UI snippet showing a cascading text message triage flow.
*   **Block B (1/3 width, Top): Review Routing**
    *   *Headline:* Reputation on Autopilot.
    *   *Body:* The second a job is marked 'Complete', we send a frictionless review request. Happy customers hit Google; frustrated ones route privately to your operations manager.
    *   *Visual:* A glowing, five-star Google review widget over an Obsidian background.
*   **Block C (Full width, Bottom): Pipeline Operations**
    *   *Headline:* The Command Center for your Crew.
    *   *Body:* Drag-and-drop scheduling, instant dispatching, and secure payment processing in one single pane of glass. Built for the front seat of a truck.
    *   *Visual:* A dense, Airtable-style grid showing Job Status, Technician, and Value.

### Section 5: The Workflow Comparison (The "Vercel" Finish)
*Purpose: The exact old vs. new state.*
*   **H2:** Shift from manual chaos to automated structure.

| The Old Way (Manual) | The NexaOS Way (Automated) |
| :--- | :--- |
| Missed calls go to a full voicemail box. | Instant text-back engages the caller in 2 seconds. |
| Relying on dispatchers to remember follow-ups. | Automated pipeline rules push jobs forward. |
| Begging customers for reviews manually. | Frictionless, automated SMS review requests post-job. |
| Disconnected tools for scheduling, SMS, and CRM. | One unified platform for your entire operation. |

### Section 6: Bottom CTA
*   **H2:** Build a business that runs itself.
*   **Subhead:** Implement NexaOS in 30 minutes and recover your first lost job today.
*   **CTA:** Start Operating
*   *Subtext:* No credit card required. Cancel anytime.

